{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1110,"text":"They told me that I'm a traitor\nto my own profession,"},{"time":5770,"text":"that I should be fired,"},{"time":7322,"text":"have my medical license taken away,"},{"time":9961,"text":"that I should go back to my own country."},{"time":14375,"text":"My email got hacked."},{"time":16018,"text":"In a discussion forum for other doctors,"},{"time":19160,"text":"someone took credit\nfor \"Twitter-bombing\" my account."},{"time":23521,"text":"Now, I didn't know if this\nwas a good or bad thing,"},{"time":26044,"text":"but then came the response:"},{"time":28331,"text":"\"Too bad it wasn't a real bomb.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":32569,"text":"I never thought that I would do something"},{"time":34600,"text":"that would provoke this level of anger\namong other doctors."},{"time":38369,"text":"Becoming a doctor was my dream."},{"time":40574,"text":"I grew up in China,"},{"time":41875,"text":"and my earliest memories\nare of being rushed to the hospital"},{"time":45243,"text":"because I had such bad asthma\nthat I was there nearly every week."},{"time":49441,"text":"I had this one doctor, Dr. Sam,\nwho always took care of me."},{"time":52517,"text":"She was about the same age as my mother."},{"time":54556,"text":"She had this wild, curly hair,"},{"time":56626,"text":"and she always wore\nthese bright yellow flowery dresses."},{"time":60027,"text":"She was one of those doctors who,"},{"time":61991,"text":"if you fell and you broke your arm,"},{"time":64110,"text":"she would ask you why you weren't laughing"},{"time":66427,"text":"because it's your humerus. Get it?"},{"time":70312,"text":"See, you'd groan,"},{"time":72054,"text":"but she'd always make you feel better\nafter having seen her."},{"time":75546,"text":"Well, we all have that childhood hero"},{"time":77556,"text":"that we want to grow up\nto be just like, right?"},{"time":80188,"text":"Well, I wanted to be just like Dr. Sam."},{"time":83634,"text":"When I was eight,\nmy parents and I moved to the U.S.,"},{"time":87404,"text":"and ours became\nthe typical immigrant narrative."},{"time":89668,"text":"My parents cleaned hotel rooms\nand washed dishes and pumped gas"},{"time":94186,"text":"so that I could pursue my dream."},{"time":97213,"text":"Well, eventually I learned enough English,"},{"time":99495,"text":"and my parents were so happy"},{"time":101026,"text":"the day that I got into medical school\nand took my oath of healing and service."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106350,"text":"But then one day, everything changed."},{"time":109495,"text":"My mother called me to tell me\nthat she wasn't feeling well,"},{"time":112305,"text":"she had a cough that wouldn't go away,\nshe was short of breath and tired."},{"time":115836,"text":"Well, I knew that my mother was someone\nwho never complained about anything."},{"time":119467,"text":"For her to tell me\nthat something was the matter,"},{"time":122038,"text":"I knew something had to be really wrong."},{"time":124359,"text":"And it was:"},{"time":125678,"text":"We found out that she had\nstage IV breast cancer,"},{"time":128835,"text":"cancer that by then had spread\nto her lungs, her bones, and her brain."},{"time":134050,"text":"My mother was brave,\nthough, and she had hope."},{"time":136214,"text":"She went through surgery and radiation,"},{"time":138195,"text":"and was on her third round of chemotherapy"},{"time":140574,"text":"when she lost her address book."},{"time":142761,"text":"She tried to look up her oncologist's\nphone number on the Internet"},{"time":145860,"text":"and she found it,\nbut she found something else too."},{"time":148433,"text":"On several websites,"},{"time":149938,"text":"he was listed as a highly paid\nspeaker to a drug company,"},{"time":153493,"text":"and in fact often spoke on behalf"},{"time":155417,"text":"of the same chemo regimen\nthat he had prescribed her."},{"time":158973,"text":"She called me in a panic,"},{"time":160570,"text":"and I didn't know what to believe."},{"time":162288,"text":"Maybe this was the right\nchemo regimen for her,"},{"time":164541,"text":"but maybe it wasn't."},{"time":166822,"text":"It made her scared and it made her doubt."},{"time":169972,"text":"When it comes to medicine,"},{"time":171682,"text":"having that trust is a must,"},{"time":174292,"text":"and when that trust is gone,\nthen all that's left is fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179750,"text":"There's another side to this fear."},{"time":181817,"text":"As a medical student, I was taking care\nof this 19-year-old"},{"time":185000,"text":"who was biking back to his dorm"},{"time":186499,"text":"when he got struck and hit,"},{"time":188638,"text":"run over by an SUV."},{"time":191166,"text":"He had seven broken ribs,"},{"time":192852,"text":"shattered hip bones,"},{"time":194225,"text":"and he was bleeding inside\nhis belly and inside his brain."},{"time":197424,"text":"Now, imagine being his parents"},{"time":199208,"text":"who flew in from Seattle,\n2,000 miles away,"},{"time":201368,"text":"to find their son in a coma."},{"time":203764,"text":"I mean, you'd want to find out\nwhat's going on with him, right?"},{"time":206771,"text":"They asked to attend our bedside rounds"},{"time":208689,"text":"where we discussed\nhis condition and his plan,"},{"time":210891,"text":"which I thought was a reasonable request,"},{"time":212888,"text":"and also would give us\na chance to show them"},{"time":214938,"text":"how much we were trying\nand how much we cared."},{"time":217389,"text":"The head doctor, though, said no."},{"time":220290,"text":"He gave all kinds of reasons."},{"time":221932,"text":"Maybe they'll get in the nurse's way."},{"time":223814,"text":"Maybe they'll stop students\nfrom asking questions."},{"time":227950,"text":"He even said,"},{"time":229387,"text":"\"What if they see mistakes and sue us?\""},{"time":233595,"text":"What I saw behind every excuse\nwas deep fear,"},{"time":236777,"text":"and what I learned\nwas that to become a doctor,"},{"time":239499,"text":"we have to put on our white coats,"},{"time":241340,"text":"put up a wall, and hide behind it."},{"time":245459,"text":"There's a hidden epidemic in medicine."},{"time":248367,"text":"Of course, patients are scared\nwhen they come to the doctor."},{"time":251182,"text":"Imagine you wake up\nwith this terrible bellyache,"},{"time":253556,"text":"you go to the hospital,"},{"time":254742,"text":"you're lying in this strange place,\nyou're on this hospital gurney,"},{"time":257994,"text":"you're wearing this flimsy gown,"},{"time":259550,"text":"strangers are coming\nto poke and prod at you."},{"time":261709,"text":"You don't know what's going to happen."},{"time":263554,"text":"You don't even know if you're going to get\nthe blanket you asked for 30 minutes ago."},{"time":267532,"text":"But it's not just patients who are scared;"},{"time":269793,"text":"doctors are scared too."},{"time":271660,"text":"We're scared of patients\nfinding out who we are"},{"time":274526,"text":"and what medicine is all about."},{"time":276656,"text":"And so what do we do?"},{"time":278247,"text":"We put on our white coats\nand we hide behind them."},{"time":281253,"text":"Of course, the more we hide,"},{"time":282962,"text":"the more people want to know\nwhat it is that we're hiding."},{"time":285761,"text":"The more fear then spirals\ninto mistrust and poor medical care."},{"time":289213,"text":"We don't just have a fear of sickness,"},{"time":291489,"text":"we have a sickness of fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295330,"text":"Can we bridge this disconnect"},{"time":297316,"text":"between what patients need\nand what doctors do?"},{"time":301135,"text":"Can we overcome the sickness of fear?"},{"time":303913,"text":"Let me ask you differently:"},{"time":305280,"text":"If hiding isn't the answer,\nwhat if we did the opposite?"},{"time":309103,"text":"What if doctors were to become\ntotally transparent with their patients?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":314531,"text":"Last fall, I conducted\na research study to find out"},{"time":317272,"text":"what it is that people want\nto know about their healthcare."},{"time":320128,"text":"I didn't just want to study\npatients in a hospital,"},{"time":322514,"text":"but everyday people."},{"time":323965,"text":"So my two medical students,\nSuhavi Tucker and Laura Johns,"},{"time":327137,"text":"literally took their research\nto the streets."},{"time":329532,"text":"They went to banks,\ncoffee shops, senior centers,"},{"time":333271,"text":"Chinese restaurants and train stations."},{"time":337191,"text":"What did they find?"},{"time":338593,"text":"Well, when we asked people,"},{"time":339962,"text":"\"What do you want to know\nabout your healthcare?\""},{"time":342388,"text":"people responded with what they want\nto know about their doctors,"},{"time":346086,"text":"because people understand health care"},{"time":347883,"text":"to be the individual interaction\nbetween them and their doctors."},{"time":351864,"text":"When we asked, \"What do you\nwant to know about your doctors?\""},{"time":354787,"text":"people gave three different answers."},{"time":356515,"text":"Some want to know\nthat their doctor is competent"},{"time":359308,"text":"and certified to practice medicine."},{"time":361614,"text":"Some want to be sure\nthat their doctor is unbiased"},{"time":364020,"text":"and is making decisions\nbased on evidence and science,"},{"time":367418,"text":"not on who pays them."},{"time":369544,"text":"Surprisingly to us,"},{"time":371104,"text":"many people want to know\nsomething else about their doctors."},{"time":374618,"text":"Jonathan, a 28-year-old law student,"},{"time":377250,"text":"says he wants to find someone\nwho is comfortable with LGBTQ patients"},{"time":382026,"text":"and specializes in LGBT health."},{"time":384659,"text":"Serena, a 32-year-old accountant,"},{"time":386401,"text":"says that it's important to her\nfor her doctor to share her values"},{"time":389726,"text":"when it comes to reproductive choice\nand women's rights."},{"time":393634,"text":"Frank, a 59-year-old\nhardware store owner,"},{"time":395815,"text":"doesn't even like going to the doctor"},{"time":398155,"text":"and wants to find someone\nwho believes in prevention first,"},{"time":401699,"text":"but who is comfortable\nwith alternative treatments."},{"time":404803,"text":"One after another,\nour respondents told us"},{"time":407143,"text":"that that doctor-patient relationship\nis a deeply intimate one —"},{"time":410621,"text":"that to show their doctors their bodies"},{"time":412587,"text":"and tell them their deepest secrets,"},{"time":414555,"text":"they want to first understand\ntheir doctor's values."},{"time":417627,"text":"Just because doctors\nhave to see every patient"},{"time":420585,"text":"doesn't mean that patients\nhave to see every doctor."},{"time":423170,"text":"People want to know\nabout their doctors first"},{"time":425388,"text":"so that they can make an informed choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428792,"text":"As a result of this, I formed a campaign,"},{"time":430968,"text":"Who's My Doctor?"},{"time":432442,"text":"that calls for total\ntransparency in medicine."},{"time":435302,"text":"Participating doctors voluntarily disclose"},{"time":437534,"text":"on a public website"},{"time":438927,"text":"not just information\nabout where we went to medical school"},{"time":441683,"text":"and what specialty we're in,"},{"time":443029,"text":"but also our conflicts of interest."},{"time":444982,"text":"We go beyond\nthe Government in the Sunshine Act"},{"time":447446,"text":"about drug company affiliations,"},{"time":449883,"text":"and we talk about how we're paid."},{"time":452887,"text":"Incentives matter."},{"time":454431,"text":"If you go to your doctor\nbecause of back pain,"},{"time":456618,"text":"you might want to know he's getting paid\n5,000 dollars to perform spine surgery"},{"time":460447,"text":"versus 25 dollars to refer you\nto see a physical therapist,"},{"time":464241,"text":"or if he's getting paid the same thing\nno matter what he recommends."},{"time":468549,"text":"Then, we go one step further."},{"time":471247,"text":"We add our values\nwhen it comes to women's health,"},{"time":473959,"text":"LGBT health, alternative medicine,"},{"time":476180,"text":"preventive health,\nand end-of-life decisions."},{"time":479191,"text":"We pledge to our patients\nthat we are here to serve you,"},{"time":482711,"text":"so you have a right to know who we are."},{"time":485456,"text":"We believe that transparency\ncan be the cure for fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489555,"text":"I thought some doctors would sign on\nand others wouldn't,"},{"time":492266,"text":"but I had no idea of the huge backlash\nthat would ensue."},{"time":497480,"text":"Within one week of starting\nWho's My Doctor?"},{"time":499719,"text":"Medscape's public forum"},{"time":501230,"text":"and several online doctors' communities"},{"time":503260,"text":"had thousands of posts about this topic."},{"time":507021,"text":"Here are a few."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508288,"text":"From a gastroenterologist in Portland:"},{"time":510548,"text":"\"I devoted 12 years of my life\nto being a slave."},{"time":513760,"text":"I have loans and mortgages."},{"time":515707,"text":"I depend on lunches from\ndrug companies to serve patients.\""},{"time":519985,"text":"Well, times may be hard for everyone,"},{"time":522251,"text":"but try telling your patient"},{"time":523972,"text":"making 35,000 dollars a year\nto serve a family of four"},{"time":526986,"text":"that you need the free lunch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530708,"text":"From an orthopedic surgeon in Charlotte:"},{"time":533041,"text":"\"I find it an invasion of my privacy\nto disclose where my income comes from."},{"time":537639,"text":"My patients don't disclose\ntheir incomes to me.\""},{"time":541202,"text":"But your patients' sources of income\ndon't affect your health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545737,"text":"From a psychiatrist in New York City:"},{"time":547932,"text":"\"Pretty soon we will have to disclose\nwhether we prefer cats to dogs,"},{"time":551351,"text":"what model of car we drive,"},{"time":552982,"text":"and what toilet paper we use.\""},{"time":555434,"text":"Well, how you feel\nabout Toyotas or Cottonelle"},{"time":558168,"text":"won't affect your patients' health,"},{"time":560204,"text":"but your views\non a woman's right to choose"},{"time":562205,"text":"and preventive medicine\nand end-of-life decisions just might."},{"time":566501,"text":"And my favorite,\nfrom a Kansas City cardiologist:"},{"time":569374,"text":"\"More government-mandated stuff?"},{"time":572456,"text":"Dr. Wen needs to move\nback to her own country.\""},{"time":576535,"text":"Well, two pieces of good news."},{"time":578145,"text":"First of all, this is meant to be\nvoluntary and not mandatory,"},{"time":581760,"text":"and second of all, I'm American\nand I'm already here."},{"time":585040,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":593512,"text":"Within a month, my employers\nwere getting calls"},{"time":596241,"text":"asking for me to be fired."},{"time":598633,"text":"I received mail\nat my undisclosed home address"},{"time":601806,"text":"with threats to contact\nthe medical board to sanction me."},{"time":605300,"text":"My friends and family urged me\nto quit this campaign."},{"time":609200,"text":"After the bomb threat, I was done."},{"time":612823,"text":"But then I heard from patients."},{"time":614765,"text":"Over social media, a TweetChat,"},{"time":617449,"text":"which I'd learned what that was by then,"},{"time":619377,"text":"generated 4.3 million impressions,"},{"time":622867,"text":"and thousands of people wrote\nto encourage me to continue."},{"time":626772,"text":"They wrote with things like,"},{"time":628404,"text":"\"If doctors are doing something\nthey're that ashamed of,"},{"time":631530,"text":"they shouldn't be doing it.\""},{"time":634121,"text":"\"Elected officials have to disclose\ncampaign contributions."},{"time":637175,"text":"Lawyers have to disclose\nconflicts of interests."},{"time":639960,"text":"Why shouldn't doctors?\""},{"time":641782,"text":"And finally, many people wrote and said,"},{"time":644510,"text":"\"Let us patients decide"},{"time":646678,"text":"what's important\nwhen we're choosing a doctor.\""},{"time":650439,"text":"In our initial trial,"},{"time":651833,"text":"over 300 doctors have taken\nthe total transparency pledge."},{"time":656289,"text":"What a crazy new idea, right?"},{"time":658841,"text":"But actually, this is not\nthat new of a concept at all."},{"time":661822,"text":"Remember Dr. Sam, my doctor in China,"},{"time":663614,"text":"with the goofy jokes and the wild hair?"},{"time":666413,"text":"Well, she was my doctor,"},{"time":667953,"text":"but she was also our neighbor"},{"time":669499,"text":"who lived in the building\nacross the street."},{"time":671681,"text":"I went to the same school as her daughter."},{"time":674007,"text":"My parents and I trusted her"},{"time":676267,"text":"because we knew who she was\nand what she stood for,"},{"time":678663,"text":"and she had no need to hide from us."},{"time":681551,"text":"Just one generation ago,\nthis was the norm in the U.S. as well."},{"time":685221,"text":"You knew that your family doctor\nwas the father of two teenage boys,"},{"time":688697,"text":"that he quit smoking a few years ago,"},{"time":690542,"text":"that he says he's a regular churchgoer,"},{"time":692533,"text":"but you see him twice a year:\nonce at Easter"},{"time":694850,"text":"and once when his mother-in-law\ncomes to town."},{"time":698492,"text":"You knew what he was about,"},{"time":699849,"text":"and he had no need to hide from you."},{"time":702837,"text":"But the sickness of fear has taken over,"},{"time":705168,"text":"and patients suffer the consequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707859,"text":"I know this firsthand."},{"time":710130,"text":"My mother fought\nher cancer for eight years."},{"time":713070,"text":"She was a planner,"},{"time":714238,"text":"and she thought a lot\nabout how she wanted to live"},{"time":716623,"text":"and how she wanted to die."},{"time":718530,"text":"Not only did she sign advance directives,"},{"time":721101,"text":"she wrote a 12-page document\nabout how she had suffered enough,"},{"time":724951,"text":"how it was time for her to go."},{"time":727867,"text":"One day, when I was a resident physician,"},{"time":729901,"text":"I got a call to say that she was\nin the intensive care unit."},{"time":733920,"text":"By the time I got there,\nshe was about to be intubated"},{"time":737360,"text":"and put on a breathing machine."},{"time":739905,"text":"\"But this is not what she wants,\"\nI said, \"and we have documents.\""},{"time":744145,"text":"The ICU doctor looked at me in the eye,"},{"time":746891,"text":"pointed at my then 16-year-old\nsister, and said,"},{"time":751043,"text":"\"Do you remember when you were that age?"},{"time":753201,"text":"How would you have liked to grow up\nwithout your mother?\""},{"time":757568,"text":"Her oncologist was there too, and said,"},{"time":760238,"text":"\"This is your mother."},{"time":762177,"text":"Can you really face yourself\nfor the rest of your life"},{"time":764830,"text":"if you don't do everything for her?\""},{"time":768375,"text":"I knew my mother so well."},{"time":770435,"text":"I understood what\nher directives meant so well,"},{"time":773595,"text":"but I was a physician."},{"time":777413,"text":"That was the single hardest\ndecision I ever made,"},{"time":781884,"text":"to let her die in peace,"},{"time":784933,"text":"and I carry those words\nof those doctors with me"},{"time":787633,"text":"every single day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791142,"text":"We can bridge the disconnect"},{"time":793356,"text":"between what doctors do\nand what patients need."},{"time":798157,"text":"We can get there,\nbecause we've been there before,"},{"time":800838,"text":"and we know that transparency\ngets us to that trust."},{"time":803331,"text":"Research has shown us\nthat openness also helps doctors,"},{"time":806096,"text":"that having open medical records,"},{"time":807702,"text":"being willing to talk\nabout medical errors,"},{"time":809739,"text":"will increase patient trust,"},{"time":811429,"text":"improve health outcomes,"},{"time":813150,"text":"and reduce malpractice."},{"time":815210,"text":"That openness, that trust,"},{"time":816749,"text":"is only going to be more important"},{"time":818423,"text":"as we move from the infectious\nto the behavioral model of disease."},{"time":822013,"text":"Bacteria may not care so much\nabout trust and intimacy,"},{"time":825487,"text":"but for people to tackle\nthe hard lifestyle choices,"},{"time":829430,"text":"to address issues like smoking cessation,"},{"time":831728,"text":"blood-pressure management\nand diabetes control,"},{"time":834765,"text":"well, that requires us to establish trust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839003,"text":"Here's what other transparent\ndoctors have said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841873,"text":"Brandon Combs, an internist in Denver:"},{"time":844790,"text":"\"This has brought me\ncloser to my patients."},{"time":847803,"text":"The type of relationship I've developed —"},{"time":850547,"text":"that's why I entered medicine.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":854117,"text":"Aaron Stupple, an internist in Denver:"},{"time":856790,"text":"\"I tell my patients\nthat I am totally open with them."},{"time":860286,"text":"I don't hide anything from them."},{"time":862360,"text":"This is me. Now tell me about you."},{"time":865286,"text":"We're in this together.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":867518,"text":"May Nguyen, a family physician in Houston:"},{"time":869920,"text":"\"My colleagues are astounded\nby what I'm doing."},{"time":873998,"text":"They ask me how I could be so brave."},{"time":876584,"text":"I said, I'm not being brave,"},{"time":879552,"text":"it's my job.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":883024,"text":"I leave you today with a final thought."},{"time":886428,"text":"Being totally transparent is scary."},{"time":889772,"text":"You feel naked, exposed and vulnerable,"},{"time":893102,"text":"but that vulnerability, that humility,"},{"time":896740,"text":"it can be an extraordinary benefit\nto the practice of medicine."},{"time":901256,"text":"When doctors are willing\nto step off our pedestals,"},{"time":903664,"text":"take off our white coats,"},{"time":905140,"text":"and show our patients who we are\nand what medicine is all about,"},{"time":908521,"text":"that's when we begin\nto overcome the sickness of fear."},{"time":911786,"text":"That's when we establish trust."},{"time":913715,"text":"That's when we change\nthe paradigm of medicine"},{"time":916175,"text":"from one of secrecy and hiding"},{"time":917985,"text":"to one that is fully open and engaged"},{"time":920344,"text":"for our patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923027,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924924,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}